ownPages.title: SingleLiveEvent
ownPages.content:
A lifecycle-aware observable that sends only new updates after subscription, used for events like navigation and Snackbar messages.

This avoids a common problem with events: on configuration change (like rotation) an update can be emitted if the observer is active. This LiveData only calls the observable if there's an explicit call to setValue() or call().

Note that only one observer is going to be notified of changes.

ownPages.title: TextViewBindings
ownPages.content:
Databinding utilities for TextView

underlineText

Underline text

Example


<layout>
...

 <!-- Result My Name -->
 <TextView
 ...
 underline="@{ `My Name` }"
 />

...
acres

Display acreage

Example


<layout>
...

 <!-- Result 3.143 Acres -->
 <TextView
 ...
 acres="@{ 3.143 }"
 />

...
setNumber

Display number by decimal places defined

Example


<layout>
...

 <!-- Result 3.14 -->
 <TextView
 ...
 number="@{ 3.143 }"
 dps="@{ 2 }"
 />

...
currency

Currency formatting by country

Example


<layout>
...

 <!-- Result UGX 10,000 -->
 <TextView
 ...
 currency="@{ 10000 }"
 country="@{ `Uganda` }"
 />

...
currencyCode

Display currency code for country e.g UGX

Example


<layout>
...

 <!-- Result UGX -->
 <TextView
 ...
 currencyCode="@{ `Uganda` }"
 />

...
setDate

Util for LocalDate date formatting

Example


<layout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">

 <data>
     <variable
     name="date"
     type="java.time.LocalDate" />
 </data>

...

 <!-- Result Mar 29, 2021 -->
 <TextView
 ...
 format="@{ `MMM dd, yyyy` }"
 date="@{ date }"
 />

...
setDate

Util for ZonedDateTime date formatting

Example


<layout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">

 <data>
     <variable
     name="date"
     type="java.time.ZonedDateTime" />
 </data>

...

 <!-- Result Mar 29, 2021 -->
 <TextView
 ...
 format="@{ `MMM dd, yyyy` }"
 date="@{ date }"
 />

...
